,Not Recommended,238430,21246589,"Posted: 15 February, 2016",all,[HomuHomu] IJ,"Pros:-Different take on a zombie killer is a breath of fresh air.-Players' ability to be common zombies is definitely another breath of fresh air.-Workshop support, and by extension, modability.-To make up for the difficulty of hosting games over the Internet (details below), it does have rather decent single-player gameplay.Cons:-Seems to need a powerful computer and graphics subsystem to play, i.e. something more powerful than even L4D2 needs.-No lobby to gather friends or other players in.-Woefully lacking network support that other Source games have makes it really difficult to host games over the Internet.  Needs either Hamachi, NeoRouter, Evolve, Tunngle, or router/firewall portforwarding/port unblocking wizardry to work at all, let alone well.-No Linux dedicated server.  Most dedicated server establishments are built on Linux owing to the expense of getting a Windows license, not to mention the fact that the best place for a Windows system is behind a heavily-fortified firewall.-In light of the above, the price on a game this modern might scare off others.  Were this in GoldSrc, I'd give it a pass.  Not this time.A mixed bag, but the best time to pick up this game is when it has a very steep discount applied to it, i.e. during seasonal and ""special event"" sales.  Until these deficiencies are addressed, my thumb goes down."
