,Not Recommended,238430,17314486,"Posted: 31 July, 2015",all,Peashooter,"Many of my friends and I are into zombie co-op games, so naturally Contagion is one of the titles which we would try on. Before I begin on descirbing the game itself, the first thing I would like to mention is that the number of people on my friend list who has the game, which is 21, is higher than the number of total players currently in game at the time I am writing this review. So, unless you can find yourself a good team (this is an 8 player co-op zombie killing game), please be prepared to face zombie hordes yourself. There will be one or two players in certain servers, but they will most likely leave half way or rambo about and turn into a zombie before you can realize what is going on. You will be real luckly if you can meet a quality player or two in any server. Truth to be told, this game has seen better days in terms of player count.There are some merits to the game itself. First of all, as a realistic zombie apocalypse co-op game, the game is rather well-made, graphically speaking. The game itself uses the source engine, so expect something along the line of Left 4 Dead. The game mechanism is rather simple and bare, so as to make sure that you don't get too much on-screen help. There will only be a health and stamina bar; you can carry 4 items of all types, some essential in solving in-game quests; you will only be able to see the silhouettes of items when you go near them. Realism, so yes, that's all you get. The enemies are simpler as well, as there will only be two types of zombies, one the normal ones where you can kill with a bullet in the head, if you are able to place it there accurately that is. The other is a ""riot police"" zombie, which soaks a lot more lead before you can kill it. Bullets are as scarce as they are sacred in the game, so think before you shoot if you can help it. Oh and you won't have a crosshair so you will need to depend on iron sights unless you are using a shotgun.Having said all that, the game itself is really not bad, though there are major problems elsewhere. Firstly, this game has a poor finishing. In the game I was playing before writing this review (and left because I was alone and I got overran halfway), I was pushed down a ladder by a zombie. That wasn't the problem, the problem is that, after being pushed down and suffering some dammage, my gun model disappeared! It won't be much of a problem if this is another game, but do not forget that Contagion does not offer any corsshair. So, what happened is that, I can't use my iron sight because the model has disappeared! The problem was solved by switching to another item (a card-key) and back, but shouldn't this bug be fixed at some point? Also, I have had issues with map skins. I was playign an official map and all reflective surfaces (and glasses) turned cyan after I did some alt-tabbing. You will know that vision is real important in this game if you are familiar with it, and it is not a simple matter of being irritating when glasses turn into solid cyan. If you can't see what's behind, hordes can close in a lot easier. Trust me, it's fatal.And did I mention that zombies tend to get stuck a lot? Yeah, though I am not complaining.Also, let's not forget that Contagion has an extremely weak game community. There's just a handful of players here and there, and there really isn't much of a back-up community to support the game. Not much custom maps, same old boring official maps with the same quests again and again, it gets repetitive. There are some die-hard fans, though most of the players I met are those who came back after a year or so to clear everything again, and then leaving it to gather dust in the vitural game shelf. I am one of them.So, my final words will be that, do not get the game unless you know what is going on and what you will be expecting. You'll most likely enjoy a lone adventure for an hour, maybe with a random teammate or two who has 300 ping, and then grow bored with it pretty soon. Nothing too fancy about this game that is worth the money."
,Recommended,238430,29056683,Posted: 6 January,all,8sianDude,"Contagion is a zombie game that offers you several game modes and maps to explore and survive the rise of the infecteds in game modes such as Escape and Extraction. The gameplay is relatively slower paced in modes like Escape as compared to other zombie games like No More Room in Hell and Left 4 Dead 2. In Hunted mode, you're placed with not just the threat of zombies, but also your fellow survivors trying to hunt you down. Not to mention, you can also play as one of the zombies when you died as a survivor, hence providing you the ability to command other zombies to hunt down your former survivor friends. Furthermore, you can also play as a cockroach instead of the typical and boring spectator camera.Pros:*Devs did a great effort in producing a game with an apocalypstic atmosphere with the great use of lighting and eerie background music.*Offers many game modes and several maps to survive.*Every time you play Escape and Extraction, objectives are shifted which provides you with unique pathways to explore the world of the living dead.*A large variety of weapons to choose from.*Instead of waiting for the game to finish after you died as a survivor, you can play as a zombie.*You can play as a cockroach instead of becoming a boring spectator camera.*Has steam workshop to customise your game.Cons:*Some guns seems to be unfinished. e.g. when unloading the Remington 870, the racking sound of the pump cannot be heard, unlike the Mossberg 590.*The Scar-L's suppressor doesn't actually reduce the noise effect of the gun on the zombies, but rather attract more zombies.*Some melee weapons have their sound misplaced in the animation, especially performing a stealth kill on the zombies. e.g. baseball bat.*Lack of updates and new contents for the game which the devs had promised.*Some maps such as Barlowe Square can be a maze in game modes such as Escape, which can be hideous sometimes when you try to complete an objective.*Some maps such as Roanoke PD has a bug where you can sometimes hear the helicopter's sound on the roof even though it has not spawned yet. Likewise, when you enter back into the police station building after the trip to the roof, the roof environment sound can still be heard.*When you spawn into an Escape game, you start at the beginning of the map, regardless of how many objectives other players had completed. This can be annoying when you try to catch up to other survivors.*Has a bug where zombies can sometimes get stuck in some places of the map. Such as windows or furniture when they're spawned.All in all, I still personally enjoy this game regardless of the unfinished contents, bugs and lack of new updates. Its still fun to play with your friends and a game worth a try if you're into zombie, horror and survival games.Rate: 6.5/10"
