 review.the animations are really good because they utilise the source engine effectivelyNope, they are not. You can take a look at cinematic SFM release trailer as a sample of animations and I really doubt that a living being is able to perform such oddities. In game reloading, moving and head bobbing (which failes to turn off when turned off in options forsome reason) are awful.With same success I may ""utilise the whole collection of my crayons effectively"" to draw a doodle on my wall.This game will always be ""in development""And I really hope that it will be in development for, at least, two more years.Full release and exit from the Early Access status usually means that all or most of planned features were implented in game. A good developers adds the minimal ammount of bugs to this checklist as well.This is clearly not a case here. I own this game for few months already and I keep receiving 250MB-400MB updates from time to time.This game is crawling with game breaking bugs.The day I bought this game I had no sounds at all available in game, which was reported by many other users as well.In same version survivors were able to climb on the weapon's shop on Barlove Square, where no zombie could reach them.In same version survivor could be trapped inside the objective without ability to leave it in rescue game mode.In same version zombies had 8 audio files, which makes approximetly 20% of current zombie sounds.In same version boltcutters/keys failed to drop from the deceased survivor, which made it impossible to complete the escape game mode.In same version it was possible to delay the infection by allowing the zombie to bite you again, while pressing the movement button.Does not sounds like a good experience, eh?Some of them were fixed in recent 200MB patches, some are still available for experiencing and dozens of new ones are added each patch.Bloody hell, they are still adding the maps (which are very few for now) and game mods after the ""full release""!Cont