,Recommended,238430,15716077,"Posted: 6 May, 2015",all,AgentEasyMark,"The game is...okay, by zombie standards. Nothing super impressive. See a zombie? Kill it. Oh! See another? Kill that one, too. Its the usual run-of-the-mill zombie killing fest we have seen on the uprise the past few years. Graphics are a little dated, being Source and all, although Source is indeed a friendly engine, they should have waited for Source Engine 2 to come out.Animations are very stiff, even for a zombie game. Zombie motions seem generic. Although it could be a placeholer for more intricate animations later on, so it is tolerable. Its small details that are easy to overlook. Glitches with holding certain weapons/items are apparent (Wielding a fire extinguisher like a shotgun, for example, or the third person melee swing animations never matching first person animations, which causes hit registration problems in online play, only. Single player is unaffected to my knowledge)The sound quality is grainy, unfortunately. The Moans/groans of the zombies can sometimes (about 40 percent of the time) overlap, causing a sound that is akin to flies buzzing in your ear. Most of the time, though, it is drowned out with gunshots and player dialogue. The Player Dialogue, though, is limited at this stage, although there is much room for improvement. Certain situations like finding weapons could in the future have callouts (Like ""Hey, shotgun here if anyone needs it!"" Or ""Pistol ammo, here!"" Or something similar, since most of it can be overlooked by mistake by players that are not as aware) Now, one feature that I would love to see would be a voice feature to attract zombies.Picture, if you will, a scenerio where one player has very low health, most of the team can escape, but this one guy, one good hit and he is gone. He could use the last of his life to go on voice chat and use his actual voice (through the computer microphone) to attract the horde towards him, thus allowing the rest of the team to get to safety (Make an achievement for this, perhaps, too?)DLC Announcements for this game were announced mid to late 2014, and were pushed back, I am certain there were reasons beyond what has been stated. Maybe so, maybe not, is that our concern? No. Things happen. It is a part of life.There are some issues with voice chat, although, from the developer response, it is from the limitations of the Engine itself, not to any fault of theirs. Solution? Use TeamSpeak or another outside client, seeing as this game was more meant to be played with friends, rather than total strangers.All things considered, the game DOES have massive potential that has yet to be tapped into! Tatsur0 and group, I apologize about any misunderstandings before, and I wish you the best of luck in the future of Contagion! I will change and add to this review as the game develops. I cannot wait to see what you have in store for us!"
