,Recommended,238430,9872706,"Posted: 19 April, 2014",all,[F!] Aldershot,"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=U9YS1ZB5Bb8Above is my impression of the game.Contagion at first glance might seem like Left 4 Dead, but when you get into it, it's actually very different from the L4D series. Rather than a linear map, or run and gun game play, Contagion features an open map level design, and conserving resources such as ammo is key to your success. The game can get hectic with 8 player multiplayer and will involve some discovery by the player to progress through the game. It still has a few rough edges here and there, but overall it's a pretty enjoyable experience.Pros:- Open world environments- Co-op or PvP game modes- Interesting player to zombie game mechanics- procedurally generated objectives and item placementCons:- Open world can leave players lost at times- A few bugs and quirks that still need ironing out- Zombie game play lack luster after a couple of tries"
