,Recommended,238430,19013396,"Posted: 11 November, 2015",all,Ersatz Soul,"This game is about survivors and zombies. Typical. First-person shooter, focused on surviving rather than l4d-styled zed slaughter, thought amount of zeds you need to kill is pretty high. What does this game offer:- mostly possible to kill zeds with only headshots or explosives (body shots will deal quite little damage, melee mostly effective on head too);- @40 minutes long maps (varies depending on knowing map, amount of players etc, good team can run escape in @20);- multiple game modes:Escape: follow 1 of 2 possible routes in zed-infested areas to escape;Extraction: find survivors and extract them;Hunted: pvp, where you kill other players (and then they spawn as PZ and try to kill others too);Panic: objectives (player zeds and survivors only, like escape) and classic (1 turning into armored zed and taking down others survivors, till noone left or zed life/time out). Shame, but almost noone plays it now - thought it's kinda quite funny mode;Flatline - currently in beta. This mode is somewhat between NMRiH survival maps and Killing floor: zombies come in waves and you need to fight them off. From NMRiH there are traps in map, from KF - shop between rounds (shop is take what you can, no money required and items are rather unlimited, but seems anything dropped in shop area being wiped out).- 4 difficulty levels, which influence amount of zeds, their attack power, friendly fire, amount of guns and ammo spawned on map (however, PZ lmb attack seems to deal constant damage for any difficulty - only bite [rmb from behind] might be affected in terms of damage, since infection chance does increase);- Equipment: few guns to shoot (3 rifles, 3 auto rifles, 2 explosives, 2 SMGs, 3 shotguns, 3 pistols for 2 types of ammo summary, bow and crossbow) - some even with flashlight attachment, and melee weapons to swing (ineffective unless fully charged head hit or special takedown from behind). Also, sometimes other equipment(gasmask and pocket flashlight you cannot put in pocket xd, wielder for making barricades at doors and windows, keys and keycards, fire extinguishers and boltcutters);- few mods from workshop (mostly - damned useless anime background for phone);- upon death/infection - turning into player zombie and hunting survivors down (or being killed by them and then being roach-spectator after few tries);- decent graphics;- only english as supported language;- zombies: casual, a bit faster, armored (no headshot and backstab instant kill) and player zombie. Sometimes, when ppl cannot use shotgun properly(or going for achievement), crawling zombies.- cards and achievements (atm no achievements for finishing new maps yet);- dedicated official servers for each map and mode, as well as some private servers;- after a while, it's a bit bothersome to play all over the same maps - but it's issue for all games;- not big number of players online - many note this issue, thought i rarely cannot find ppl to play with.Personal opinion - game is somewhat between L4D and No More Room in Hell: alot of guns and ammo for them, alot zombies you need to kill, but mostly only headshots can bring them down and melee isnt 1hit. What i find disappointing - ability to carry 3 assault rifles (98 bullets in) + 150 bullets for them + smg (30 bullets in) + 150 bullets for smg when u`re average Joe without much of pockets and backpack (NMRIH is free zed game and has nice solution for this 1 issue, but has oldest graphics, which is focused on mostly avoiding, not killing everything). Still, for teamwork and shooting zeds game is sufficient enough.However, do note, that you need to train ur skills to land headshots and playing with random people is sometimes.....annoying. If you have some friends you want to play this game with - then it's good, since having team w teamwork can save the day.special note: promised by devs, ALL dlcs and updates are free. So far i have this game - true. Recently they've added few maps and guns and going to add flatline mode.As for soundtrack - well, typical, but when they published it - on-date owners got it for free. Also, it's much cheaper than in other games."
