,Recommended,238430,8058868,"Posted: 15 December, 2013",all,Redruler,"When first playing Contagion, I thought to myself, ""Oh a slower left 4 dead"".  And while that might be true, Contagion is also a lot more.The game is still in ""Early Access Beta"", and so far it is shaping up to be quite promising.  My favorite mode is ""Escape"".  You need to work with your team mates, watch each other's backs, and... escape.  The slow pacing adds to the sense of dread and paranoia that will hit you while you scavange for a few more bullets and try to find the way out.  The smart phone your character carries provides objective updates and on some modes a map and GPS directions.Reaching the end and escaping is highly satisfying after the methodical gameplay and teamwork you need to use to get there.  Once more maps are added it will only improve this great game even more.This game is well worth the price of entry and a steal if you can get it on sale."
