76561197969276367,Recommended,238430,9617704,"Posted: 24 March, 2014",all,Frengler,"Inevitably this game will be compared up against Left 4 Dead 2. This is understandable but not entirely fair to the game although there are certainly many similarities. In a market already oversaturated with zombie-games left, right and center what is there to recommend? What is there to make this stand out? Honestly I can't answer that since I haven't played most of the other games out there. What I can tell you though is why I like it.First of all it has atmosphere in spades. The graphics do a lot to help with this and by that I don't necessarily mean visual fidelity but the overall style. Where L4D is a little lighter on the horror and as a result tend to be a brighter game this is darker and more - dare I call it - ""realistic"". When I say dark I mean litteral darkness and your flashlight is designed in such a way that it isn't a magic lamp that illuminates everything and make things instantly better. You'll have to see it to know what I mean but I can tell you that facing off against a gang of zombies in a dark room can get very tense despite your flashlight.The pace is also very different. It's slower and less arcade than other similar FPS zombie games. Zombies move slower and though they can ""run"" (more like walking fast) there are no sprinters. It builds more on the premise that even a few zombies become a serious threat if you let them come up close. Headshots are the name of the game and ammo/weapons are meant to be scarce. Melee is an option but don't expect to wade through even a few zombies with your sledgehammer. Zombies take multiple hits to go down, swings are slower than you might think... oh and they use precious stamina that you also need to sprint.I could go on but I hope the above has already given you a sense of whether this is something for you or not. You can read about the different game modes elsewhere but in brief there's one PvP mode (hunting others on maps filled with zombies) and two co-op modes. And when I say co-op I do mean co-op: don't expect to get far or have an easy time without some serious teamwork!Bottom-line: don't let comparisons to other games (such as L4D1-2) influence your decision. Both this game and L4D2 are among my favorite zombie co-op shooters and I love each for their way of doing things."
