76561198044058707,Not Recommended,238430,20205475,"Posted: 1 January, 2016",all,Orthallon,"The game is entertaining and has many great features, but it has many bugs including the following:1. Sometimes the keyboard/mouse will not move you correctly after loading; disabling controller settings can help this however these settings are on by default and it may be a recurring problem if you are not diligent about checking them.2. There is no way to tell if you are going to spawn as a zombie when joining random games, so if you're interested in cooperative play to meet objectives, you need to arrange your match ahead of time for any guarantees.3. Every time I have completed a map, the game sits on the final score screen and I am forced to exit the game which results in my not having any of my achievements recorded on my steam profile.  Annoying to not be able to track your progress.4. Between my kids and I (three computers), whenever we try to play together on LAN, if one of the games crashes it crashes the game for all three of us.  The two who do not crash get a ""Game Paused"" message and it never recovers, and the person who crashed (if it was not the host) is unable to rejoin the game.  We have not yet been able to complete a mission together on LAN due to this.  This may actually be two problems; either an actual game crash, or a short break in our wifi which I believe is the cause for the ""Game Pause"" message, however both have the same result of being unable to finish a level.If these issues can be resolved then I would recommend this game."
