,Recommended,238430,11954000,"Posted: 1 September, 2014",all,Madface,"If you're looking at this you're probably wondering if the game is worth a buy, 20$ may seem very expensive to those who don't have the luxury to just go out and buy games without a doubt while it may seem like pocket change to others.Considering this is my first review please take this with a grain of salt.Why should I consider buying Contagion?You should buy Contagion because It's fun, it provides an environment where cooperation is key, while that may seem like a generic statement across all sorts of zombie survival games, seriously, in this one, it is. If your friends die they become zombies and ultimately that makes your gameplay a whole lot more difficult because that one player zombie can infect another player and they're count goes up one by one until the last person is left cowering in a corner before she/he is mauled to death by a horde. A lot of players who prefer the old slow zombies and freakish hordes of them will like this game in its entirety.Contagion challenges the players in a multitude of gamemodes such as...Escape - Which you could say is the traditional left 4 dead style,""Let's go do some objectives so we can get out of here.""type of thing.Extract - If you have ever played Resident Evil 3, this is the mercenary mode where you run around extracting civilains.Hunt - You versus everything else pretty much.Zombie Panic Classic - If you have ever played the Free to Play Zombie Panic Source, this is basically the same.Zombe Panic Objective - The same as Zombie Panic Source's objective escape mode, it's Escape in Contagion too but this time it's you versus a player zombie at the start.Stopping with the possibly ranting non-sense, lets get on with this review. First of all, the store page in comparison to real gameplay.Store Page Advertising in Comparison to Real GameplayIf you've read the section ""What they're saying about Contagion"" which is the first section of the store page for reviewers it's basically saying that Contagion is a good game that has gone back to the old style slow zombie game that is worth the 20$ it's worth. But is that really true?My Experience in relation to this statement.Yes, Contagion has done that and so far I've liked the game, even in the most frustrating moments I've had fun running around popping zombies in the head once or beating them with a melee weapon of my choice. But that is me however, how would it be for you the player?Contagion may be fun for a good majority of the possible people willing to throw money at the developers so that they can play however a there is also the fact a lot of people have said that the game is terrible, the graphics are bad, the gameplay sucks, gore is 'meh' and it's been an overall bad experience. Hell, the two first reviews I saw of Contagion had said that it was a bad game and there was only one good review. But these reviews were a bit old, like, months back old so I decided to write one myself.In all seriousness, if you have a problem with graphics, any game developed for the Source Engine is gonna look bad in some way so you should save yourself the time and money and just ignore this game all together. If you're cool with it, enjoy.Gameplay wise, if you have everything going for you and you have a smart team to play with, even on the most hardest difficulties you will steam roll through zombie hordes and make it to the end with minimum casualties if not zero. That is probably the biggest aspect of the game I consider that makes it fun for anyone to play it really. Teamwork is essential in this game and if you're not a teamplayer, you're gonna get wiped quick and you'll probably get mad very easily at this game because being mauled by a horde of zombies isn't fun, not for you, not for anyone and not even for your teammates across the map. Because when you die, they'll have to deal with you and any player zombie is more fiendish than an NPC in a horde.The Gore is decent, it's not gonna rock you and have blood spraying everywhere but the limbs will fall off I assure you this. It's also toggable so if you have children who want to play feel free to turn of it. Then again, why are you subjecting your child to such a violent gorish videogame like Contagion?Overall Experience of Contagion? It's pretty good, I wouldn't say 'decent' because the only time I would ever say 'decent' if it was a 50/50 that everything was going right and everything was going wrong at that point. With my 'small' experience of Contagion gameplay I can only say this. It's good because discluding the idiotic players, the twit taking things he doesn't need and the relatively low chance of getting trolled by a zombie because you've emptied a magazine into his head, it's pretty good.The only things you need to worry about in the game is the things I just discluded, the dumb or should I say, learning players, the trolls, the hoarder of ammo and the trollish hitboxes preventing you from ending the zombies life. Those are the only things that are going to ruin your day, mostly the trollish hitboxes on the zombies. Other than that, the players tend to listen and stick together but you will usually always have the one guy who decided to hoard everything and not share one bit of it.Dynamic GameplayWhat they've said is true in terms of finding weapons or objectives but the map layout tends to be the same and you will usually have a deja vu moment here and there. It will always be new in terms of trying to find the objective in the various places they put it as well as the pathways you take to that objective but other than that the map will remain the same. I honestly thought the map would be different like they made blocks of the maps that would interlock easily and would create a whole new environment all together.Edit 9/2/2014 - Added a little bit concerning the pathways to objectives will always be different.State Of The Art GoreI would say that this would be true in terms of it described but I honestly don't think it's state of the art, you could really compare this to Deadspace's limbic system when you utterly destroyed the monsters.Immersive Sound EffectsThis I would consider to be definetly true, I never got to a point where I ran through the game without even thinking, I was always cautious because the obvious zombie moans around the corner usually prepared me to get mauled to death.Traditional ZombiesYes, yes, yes. Spot on though I'd have to say, they can climb ladders and get into vents? Seems a bit new to me in terms of what zombies could do...Extensive Survival EquipmentI'd have to say, this really disappointed me. I expected there to be a multitude of items to use as a weapon and it severely disappointed me when I enter a store and there's all this hardware I could use as a possible weapon but they didn't consider it. They did however say that they would continue to add so I suspect more in the future.Unique GamemodesI don't know if Unique meant that the experience in itself would be unique each time or that each game mode was unique. This statement is basically what I explained up top if you've missed it, other than that, I don't know how to respond to this literally.Stop Paying MoreHurray! What else am I supposed to say?I'll probably add more to this review later on in the future, overall I have to say 9/10, the game is really fun when things are on your side, that can be said for a lot of games though.In the end, it's your choice whether or not you want to buy it or not. Hopefully this review is on your side and you don't have a horrible experience."
