,Not Recommended,238430,10710247,"Posted: 23 June, 2014",all,Peter Wiggin,"I'd just like to toss in my two cents, and a hearty concurrence to the review by CunningFox.First of all, the biggest death to this game from my seasoned experience of survival gaming, is definitely the mobility. If you want to make your characters move slow for the sake of difficulty, then you need to base the entire game's format, map layouts, and zombie AI around that. Not have slow straight walking-across-open-spaces, zombies, massive spanning maps with terrible layouts, and little nooks and cranny's that are your actual necessary route, but hidden in a dark corner alleyway. You could pretty easily just melee your way through the entire map with the difficulty of the zombie pathing and behavior, so it's not like making the objectives and map routes hard to find is interesting or difficult, it's just extremely tedious. And then once you learn the route through the maps, the game becomes incredibly simple. It's just a lottery of whether humans become zombies from source external of the actual zombies attacking you; Such as joining late, or willfully being suicidal/EXTREMELY BAD AT GAMES. I mean, the first time me and my friends played escape on that city level, we actually wandered around virtually ignoring the zombies for a good 40 minutes, because the maps are just so circular fenced off in stupid places, with little hidden pathways to circumvent the randomly locked and unlocked doors.This is also so far away from realism and immersion that it becomes implausible to consider scaring or thrilling the player, and yet the genre is horror survival. Rofl. Fence gates you can't climb over, zombies that are about as threatening as counterstrike bots who aren't allowed to have guns, and the mappers in all their aesthetic glory, can't actually map at all. There's no culling, there's invisible walls everywhere because they can't design well, and random piles of debree that look like a nice one way ramp, are actually walls to prevent any access (To the other side, which is also part of the map, but you'll have to walk a big circlejerk circle around the map to get there) I can understand having restricted pathways to get to certain areas in order to make a linear pathway to a final objective, but this is definitely not how you do it. And again about the culling, that is some really terrible mapping. I go from 200fps looking in the direction of the outwards edge of the map, to 30 looking inwards. This is ♥♥♥♥ing source engine, you can take literally 3minutes to learn how to occlusively cull geometry and props, on youtube. Look up 3kliksphilip. This was a terribly impulse purchase in hopes of reigniting the days I loved on L4D in a new experience. Such good prospect, such a broken game. I was praying it was in beta or alpha stages when I closed the game and came back to the store page, because I didn't really look at anything when it was 5$Edit: Also and checking more reviews, I just had a giggle that there's two people who downvote every single negative review, for hundreds of reviews so far."
