,Recommended,238430,11953981,"Posted: 1 September, 2014",all,I look like Avril Lavigne,"I think I got this game for $4.99 or something, on sale, and it was worth every penny! At first the game was really laggy for me, but then I changed the video settings to ""very high"" and the game looked awesome and worked fine! It lags a bit from time to time but it does not hinder my performance. Lots of people play this game and most are friendly players, some people do not work well as a team... but that is the way with any cooperative gameplay and especially in a zombie game.A lot of people compare this with Left 4 Dead and a lot say otherwise, truth is Valve was also Left 4 Dead so... YES, in many aspects this game is much like Left 4 Dead. I like the levels, they are pretty big and lots of places to search, hide, snipe, etc. I enjoy most game types for this game... my biggest issue with the game overall is, being a zombie... it SUCKS! Sometimes I am spawned really far away, or in a deadend, or my scent trail runs cold and I can't track the survivors. But it has made me get better at surviving because I don't want to be a dang zombie.There are no ""special"" zombies either which I like, the only thing close to that in this game is the riot police zombie which is slow, dumb, and easy to dodge. I never liked a lot of ""special infected"" like the smoker from L4D is so unreal, or just about any special zombie in Resident Evil. There is a good selection of weapons to weild and I like that you need to find special tools for special tasks. Like you need to find a nail gun then you need to find a wood to board up windows and doorways. Or some doors are locked and you need to find a key, or bolt cutters to clip the chain on doors... pretty frustrating at times though, not finding what you need with a hoard on your tail.I would recommend this game, I have had a lot of fun with it already.Rating  7.5/10+Zombies!+Level design+Weapons & tools-Being a zombie... :{}"
