,Recommended,238430,10649464,"Posted: 21 June, 2014",all,Rasori,"A friend of mine told me to get this game awhile back, and when I was checking it out it seemed pretty cool but not amazing. I'm always cautious of early access games because you never know where your money is being spent, or if they're even working on it at all. But I risked it for this game based on the fact that it gave me and my friend something to Co-op for awhile.And I'm so glad that I did, because It's one of the best early access games I've ever played, and absolutely worth the price. I got to play it for most of it's beta, and I've seen it go from a cool little zombie game, to a game on par with L4D2. At it's current state, It's added so much more content to the game since Beta, the Developers have listened to every bug or problem I found while playing (which they'd look into and fix almost immediately) And graphically, it's the best looking game I've ever seen coming from an indie team, even better than most AAA games aswell.You can really feel how much effort they put into this game, from the subtle references of their original game Zombie Panic Source, to the finer details in lighting, textures, ambient noise and overall atmosphere. Also did I mention, you can chop the arms off a zombie, and watch as it attempts to grab you but can't? Yeahhh this game is worth your time"
