76561198038046971,Recommended,238430,12581247,"Posted: 20 October, 2014",all,Tony [Actual Skeleton],"If you're looking for complete realism, this may not be the game for you, but it comes close. If you want something as realistic as it can get (at least at the time this was written), try No more room in hell, which is free on steam. Anyway, in this game, you play as a survivor of a zombie apocalypse, where zombies are everywhere and ammo is everything but plentiful. Players can play in (Again, in the time this was written, because updates happen) 3 different gamemodes. Hunted places players in a deathmatch-like game, where you are your only friend, and the zombies aren't the only threat. Humans can fight off zombies as well as each other (Which is why I never play hunted). Objective has players meneuvering throughout a map attempting to complete a list of objectives in order to escape the nightmare. And finally, Extraction consists of players going to different locations looking for survivors, and once a group of survivors are located, players have to defend the area for a specific amount of time, after which they are escorted to an extraction point.Players who die will take control of a zombie for the rest of the game (Which is one of the reasons I find it unrealistic), and have some abilities to compensate for their very small amount of heallth (Another reason it's unrealistic). Undead players can call zombies to their aid, and can command them to attack living players, and can let the AI take over to seem like AIs to living players and lower suspicioun.IIt's a tad pricy, but it's good fun, and using a mic is recommended for communicating with your team without stopping and letting a zombie take you out."
