,Recommended,238430,7628284,"Posted: 10 November, 2013",all,lualolula,"Really fun and entertaining zombie game. Unlike many others the zombies actually ""feel"" real. They shamble through the streets, heads bobbing around like maniacs as they slowly pace toward you, making those headshots more difficult than one would imagine. Completely ignoring bullets as they rip through their arms and legs, as it has no effect other than waying their arm slightly. If you want the kill, you're going to have to get that perfect headshot.They stupidly wander aimlessly, only beginning the chase once you've alerted them by sprinting through the streets or firing like a maniac. Smashing through doors and barricades with their bleeding arms, lacking the mental capacity to use door knobs. The zombies definitely have a life-like, or rather, un-life-like quality that makes them very appealing.But the zombies aren't the only threat. Aside from the co-op ""Extraction"" and ""Escape"" game modes, ""Hunted"" brings one of the most exciting and dynamic pvp experiences. Because unlike other games, being shot down doesn't just end your life, it brings on a new one. The hunt continues as you stalk the humans from the shadows as a newly made zombie. As a human you scavenge for weapons and supplies on the spot, compulsively checking your phone for nearby survivors, or player zombies. You can run guns ablaze through the streets, hoping to run into il-prepared survivors, or barricade a house of your own and take your last stand. Shooting through windows at other survivors or battling an onslaught of zombies as they swarm their way up the stairs or bashing down the door to the room you've taken shelter in.Overall it's a great game and I strongly recommen it. However, a Mic is basically a must. While not so much if you fly solo on Hunted, but the co-op modes desperately require coordination and team work, as a well-crrafted co-op game should. Definitely better with friends. Teaming up with them as securing a house together as you battle off the undead is some of the most fun I've had in a multiplayer game.The only downside to this game is the lack of content. Which can be expected from an early-access game. There's only 3 maps as of yet, 1 of which is used in 2 of the game modes. But with steam workshop support in the works, user maps and mods, that will soon be a thing of the past. But it doesn't require that. The devs are still very much working on the game and supplying new content.Well worth the price. I'm already over 30hours of gametime and it has yet to lose it's luster. At $15, this game is a steal.8/10"
