,Recommended,238430,9841279,"Posted: 17 April, 2014",all,NightCloud,"First of all, I bought Contagion when it was in its Early Alpha stages and couldn't really play a lot of it since there weren't a lot of players and servers. But now, I found out that the game is finally released and I'm not disapointed. At first I wanted to get this game because it reminded me of The Walking Dead TV show (Which I say about a lot of zombie games but they are not as they seem to me at first) but it's not like that at all except for the ""Only headhsots kill"" rule. Now since the release a lot has changed: New and modified weapon slots which make it easier to find weapons, new zombie ""Roar"" feature which lures more zombies to the survivors to make them suffer even more, achievments, trading cards, modes and an improved intro and menu. The level section is easy to choose from, the only problem is that there still aren't many servers to play on, but if you do find one, the experience is great. The levels are never the same and the keyitems are always scattered in different locations and some pathways are closed in one playthrough but in the other they aren't. The only negative aspects I can find in this game for now are the way too overpowered human controlled zombies and the zombie spawn points. They don't die to a single headshot, no, they take an entire magazine to the face to die. They are just normal zombies to blend into the crowd and not some special infected like in Left 4 Dead, so they should have lower health and better spawn points. They can kill a human in about 2 hits and once you respawn you need to find the survivors at the other end of a totally confusing map!All in all Contagion is fun zombie game and I'd recommend it to anyone who likes zombie survival games which they can play with friends."
