,Recommended,238430,13257045,"Posted: 6 December, 2014",all,Eckk,"There really needs to be more games like Contagion. Think Left 4 Dead, but a less theatrical, and more realistic rendition of Z-Day that doesn't involve mutant monster zombies that throw rocks and spit acid. Also refreshing, is how Contagion has more of an emphasis on ammo conservation than most shooters in general, making for another layer of conflict when encountering hordes of undead. Really makes you think twice before deciding: ""Shotgun, or sledgehammer?""Zombies are not nearly as squishy as most of us would like to think, with our prior video game knowledge. While headshots are always the goal, they are pratically paramount in Contagion.Refreshingly enough, there is split screen co-op if you have a buddy and another controller. If you're playing online, that's cool too. You can have way more than 3 other buddies playing along - so there's yet another leg up on the L4D series, in my opinion. The only critique I can possibly offer for Contagion is: the lack of content. My friends and I don't really do PvP - we're more about the coop stuff. Unfortunately, there are only a handful of coop missions, and though they are rather lengthy, and they all tend to play a little differently every time, there is still something lacking with the progression. At it's core, it really just just a load of blasting, slashing, running and gunning, but there's so much potential here for something more that just isn't quite there yet. I've really been pulling through for Contagion to introduce more content, and I'm still hopeful that there's more to come, but I can't be too sure.Regardless, as is, it's still a superb game with some really tight controls and shooting mechanics. Bullet physics are wonderful, and each and every headshot you get is so satisfying that you likely won't notice until after getting a few hours in that you've been doing the same thing over and over again. One of my favorite coop games in existence. If you're looking to blast through some zombies with some friends, this is it. It's also quite pretty, to boot."
