,Not Recommended,238430,7887367,"Posted: 2 December, 2013",all,Oh Noes,"Contagion is an above average zombie survival FPS game that provides some unique gameplay elements.  I enjoyed playing this game during the beta and release and especially liked the route changes as you replay levels and the emphasis on teamwork.But I feel the full release is still in late beta because of these things:1) Game breaking bugs like zombies getting stuck, zombie players spawning in locations where they are trapped, zombie players can’t climb certain walls that the A.I. can, and a path in Barlowe Square that sometimes doesn’t open and the game is ruined.2) The overly difficult gameplay which seems to lack testing before implementation.  You probably have a 5% chance at most of winning on a public server in the PVE game modes on normal difficulty.  This is due to a lack of ammo, lack of melee weapons, easy player infection, and overpowered player zombies.  Pretty much the only way to win in PVE is to play solo or with a close group of friends.  I would strongly recommend kiting large zombie hordes, especially in Barlowe Square, kiting is an almost essential playing style and can be a huge turnoff for some players.3) There is a lack of content to justify the $20 price, although the developer has promised more free content is on the way.  I picked up the game for cheap so I can’t complain, but I feel there is not enough maps or replayability for a new buyer.4) The Hunted mode (PVP) feels ‘arcadey’ to me because points are awarded for killing zombies.  Players are encouraged to shoot zombies for points which helps move the game along at a faster pace to get to the next round.  But I feel when someone is hunting they are generally trying to be stealthy when searching for prey.  The Battle Royale mode in ARMA 3 is a similar game mode, but slower paced and a good example of how this mode should play IMO.I think this game has the potential to be great someday, especially after bug fixes, new content, and the release of the SDK.  But Contagion currently lacks polish and I can’t recommend the game for now.***The August 2014 update has made the difficulty more reasonable with more ammo and stronger melee attacks.  There is also a new map.  Game is starting to look a lot better."
