76561197969856852,Recommended,238430,9591941,"Posted: 22 March, 2014",all,Biscuit,"This game is quickly shaping up to be the zombie survival horror game that you never knew you always wanted.  This game has aspects that remind you of the past greats like Resident Evil and House of the dead, while it also incorporates elements the new classics such as L4D.  The game is a bit more slow paced, but the tension is there with all of the great ambiance and sound on par with games like Dead Island.  While the game and the zombies are a bit more slow paced, the game is very much alive with excitement as you work your way through elaborately constructed levels that can at times be a little disorienting but very much exciting.  The addition of short term goals, or mini-missions allows the payer to feel more like they are really surviving the apocolypse rather than gunning their way through a movie as in L4D.  This game is very much in the spirit of the older Dawn of the Dead zombie movies, and is a must play for anyone who enjoys that genre."
