,Recommended,238430,7876427,"Posted: 1 December, 2013",all,Guardian,"Contagion is a fun objective based zombie survival game. Minus some initial issues with crashing to the desktop before getting into the game, I'd recommend it heartily. The game rewards good observation skills and keen awareness of your surroundings. There are a couple issues with odd animations when the zombies get in close to attack or when they go to climb over something, but the sound quality is very good including some background noise such as far off gunshots, which is hard to mistake for gunshots within the map that you're playing. Good job on the sounds. The zombies sound eerie and when they spot you, you'll know it. Ammo is spread around the maps, and is sparse, but luckily, there are some decent melee weapons.For people who want to compare this to Left 4 Dead, I'd say it's a bit more easy going, but just as scary even without ""special"" infected. The maps objectives and loot is randomized throughout the map, so check your corners and behind desks because there are some surprises occasionally in the form of ammo and weapons.Multiplayer requires cooperation. Those people who run and gun getting all the loot will find themselves alone soon with the players that die taking over spots as zombies. More than a few times I was surprised by a zombie while I was going to check a dark room and it turned out a player who had died was waiting for someone.It's worth the full price of the game, although I got it at the steam sale for half off. I'd recommend it as a well thought out zombie survival game."
