,Not Recommended,238430,10853063,"Posted: 26 June, 2014",all,Sgtpanda,"A game released from early access... that still looks like it's in early access.Picked this up on sale 75% off and even then it's only just worth it, what's wrong, well:1) It doesn't look great, source engine may be old but it can still be beautiful, unfortunately this game is not an example, it's hard to put my finger on it, but all the environments feel too ""clean"", they look pristine, in fact, so much so they don't look real, especially for an apocalypse.2) The guns, they all feel like toys, cannot tell the difference between any of the pistols, the shotguns have really stupid damage (point blank to the chest wouldn't flat out kill you?) and are buggy and the sniper scope is near impossible to use.3) It really doesn't feel finished, you can do dumb stuff like run a long fences, the zombie climbing mechanic can never make it's mind up whether you can climb that thing - and will allow you to climb out of the map, and movement feels clunky. As an added bonus, as I found when launching the dedicated server, one of the things it printed to console was ""Map is missing dictionary - DON'T SHIP LIKE THIS"", even the developers don't seem to think it's finished.4) The gamemodes - Hunted just turns into free for all, Escape (I think) is just like nazi zombies but with a vending machine that randomly spits stuff out and you all end up running out of ammo, then there's another one which is ""lead the AI around"" and then there's another one which I don't even remember so it must be great.5) The phone, pretty much a gimmic, being able to ring people in hunted is good, but beyond that it just feels shoehorned in, in some missions you get to use it as a map, why not all? The game really needs one! Each time I spawn I have no idea where I am, most times because I'm in the dark.Redeeming features: If you like L4D and got bored of it then you'll probably like this for a couple of days until the four maps get repetitive - more are coming though as free DLC (DLC or 'finishing off the game'?)Oh and the English is really terrible in places and it behaves really weirdly with a controller.TL:DR Pick it up for less than £5, no more.EDIT: Proof on issue 3 -http://i.imgur.com/6Td7w0E.png"
