,Recommended,238430,17665759,"Posted: 22 August, 2015",all,Aaron,"If you've played Left 4 Dead, it's basically more of the same but with less special infected (there's only the bullet-sponge that is the riot-gear zombie) and more objectives.There are also different gamemodes available. Things like Escape, where you try to do exactly that, while completing objectives along the way (unlock this, go here, press this, hold off against these, etc), Evac, where you go around collecting survivors to escort to safety, or the true PvP gamemode where you hunt each other when you're alive and have to watch out for zombies.If a player dies, they come back as a zombie. This will usually ruin the game if you're in a small team, because for some reason they take a lot more damage. They also bob and weave which, combined with their pings, means you miss a lot before they're tearing at your face. But in a large group, it's usually not a problem.But I mostly enjoy the Escape maps. Completing objectives as they appear on the phone you use to tell you were to go has a satisfying sense of accomplishment. While you're killing zombies, you're keeping an eye out for things like key cards, boltcutters, or keys, just in case they're useful later. It brings a sense of teamwork, when each person gives up a valuable weapon slot to carry an item that we might need later. And it all comes together when you've fought through hell, got down to your last clip, and then you find a locked door that you can open with something you've saved that whole time. All the goodies waiting behind, ready to re-kit your team into killing machines.All in all, a game I enjoy wasting a couple of hours on here and there, though I would advise to wait for it to go on sale (the full price is a bit steep, in my eyes).Edit: I would like to mention this: if you become a zombie, you only get 4 lives and then you enter spectator mode for the rest of the game. A terrible idea, really, and I hope it gets changed."
76561198044797961,Recommended,238430,20455658,"Posted: 10 January, 2016",all,Jan,"A middling first person shooter of infected genre. Decent graphics and scenes, tight mechanics, big maps, classic selection of guns and tools. Light and sound effects and its consecuences are very fine finished too. Includes an option of infection risk and play as a zombie. But its quite limited for single player: hand combat is insecure, slow and without options to block or evade attacks, the stealth system is poor, guns are little useful at closer ranges and the most powerful ones attract so many foes that is better to use them only at final struggles or known places; to survive depends on random placing of medkits. Missing classic weapons of genre like flametrower, molotov cocktail, katana and chainsaw. Player can not climb fences and walls like the infected, that can to sprint and pursue players without pause, at long distances. Foes are a bit exaggerated: are infected, but they can running a lot and make strong damages with bare hands, only a headshot can kill them, like conventional zombies; some wear really heavy armours. The difficultly is bad leveled: normal is piece of cake but hard is nearby to the impossible: get cornered by two or three enemies at close range always is lethal. Could be better with more scenarios for ""escape"" mode. Causes glitches on Windows 10 and Workshop community has few mods. Very often offered with high discounts, no buy without."
