,Recommended,238430,8644780,"Posted: 10 January, 2014",all,weirdphil,"Alright, this is another survival horror FPS, the spiritual successor to Zombie Panic Source is now available via Early Access. I want to start off by saying that this game looks visually appealing. It is beautiful. There are only a few maps available at the moment, as it is in beta, but you do get a few different game modes out of it. You can escort AI-controlled survivors, battle zombies as a human or battle humans as a zombie, or my personal favorite, escape from the police department in an objective-based co-op experience. There are a lot of great ideas, and the price tag does indeed turn some people away from this game when the alternative is Free to Play. Both games are technically in beta and both will only get better in time. Contagion is a very fun experience and worth the money. It is an entirely different game than No More Room In Hell and they can't truly be compared with each other because they are trying to achieve different goals. When you die to the zombies in Contagion, your corpse will rise and you will walk among the dead. You will control your own zombie with the intention to do harm to your former allies. The levels are large, and the zombies are plentiful. You can host your own games or play on dedicated servers. If you are looking for one more push before you buy this, I strongly recommend that you check out YouTube for that last push."
