76561198078582252,Recommended,238430,9960259,"Posted: 28 April, 2014",all,Baggy,"Contagion applies the Zombie rules set out by George A. Romero. Playing Contagion brings you closer to staring in one of Romero's Dead series. With these slow(er) moving Zombies they can seem to the player at first as sitting ducks while idle, however they are numerous whereas ammo isn't. It doesn't take much to become overcome by the walking dead as they are relentless. Sometimes stealth is required, teamwork, maybe its a new use for a wrench? A gun shot carefully aimed at the brain, it has to be the safer method.But did you think of the noise it made, now nearby Zombies have been alerted to its sound and hence your whereabouts, its time to run or fight! Play in co-op, alone as a hunter in pvp up against human survivors, AI and human Zombies as death in Contagion isn't the end, just your new stumbling beginning.Contagion at this time of writing has 3 game modes*Hunted (PVP)*Excape (objective)*Extraction (Holdout)*New FREE DLC to add more maps and modes in the pipeline*SDK for user made content including maps. (check out the forums for current projects)*Currently they are 5 offical maps, 2 free addon maps. (28/04/14)*The game uses Brainboxes not to be mistaken as headshots for one shot kills.*Zombie AI is realisticly zombie like, stumbling and farting like they should. (OK I lied about the farting)*Aim down gun sights for careful placement of high speed bullet between the eyes.*Great weight to characters movements.*George A. Romero: Zombie rules applies. Big +ve.At time of review 8/10The game isn't without issues, however over look these small issues and theres a game that has a healthy level of improvements, updates, community and developer involvement. It seems to be a real labour of love for Monochrome, that isn't simpley been left to decay (pun intended)."
