76561198123004864,Recommended,238430,10067509,"Posted: 9 May, 2014",all,Bridenfelt,"I have yet to play much of Contagion, what I have played is extremely interesting and fun. The gameplay and mechanics are things I've felt would make for an amazing zombie game, and to see it utilized cements my belief. The only headshots kill is a wonderful and perfect mechanic to a zombie game and it plays well. Graphcally speaking it looks great. The atmosphere is also phenomenal. Its dark and terrifying. Perfect for a zombie survival game. Though there are a few issues.Firstly is the amount of RAM required to run this game. 4 gigs is kind of ridiculous to me. I only have 3 gigs and no other game has required that much RAM, though, I may be making more of a deal out of it than it is. Secondly is the light mechanic. Upon certain surfaces it creates a weird glare like deal along the screen and is mildly blinding. Kind of a pain to me, and I havent found a way to fix it.All in all though this is a great game at an ASTOUNDING price, and if you have the RAM, unlike me, you shouldnt have to many issues if any at all. I would highly recommend it to all gamers with a love for zombies. Buy, Install, and ENJOY my friends."
