,Recommended,238430,18033598,"Posted: 14 September, 2015",all,Toastmaster 1B14,"A wonderful, yet challenging, new twist to zombie shoot'em ups. The weapon mechanics are fun and diverse across the many different firearms, and playing with character voices on really gives you a more emersed feeling, as who you're playing as has much more of a personality as a human being, desperate to stay alive. The trailer makes it sound incredibly round based, but I beg to differ. Each playthrough of escape, for example, can take an average of half an hour. It's less of a ""round"", more of an adventurous experience, in a world that has fallen to chaos. Each map really shows how dark the apocalypse really is, with each level littered with blood pools and body bags, police cars and ambulances, death and disease. My only possible complaint is that this would be more fun if it were more of a survival experience, having to manage your own needs as a survivor, as well as defending your long-term shelter. The sound system could use some work, but something like that is hard to do.All in all, a wonderful, yet tragic, game.Also, I still haven't found that darn coin."
