,Recommended,238430,8815247,"Posted: 22 January, 2014",all,Psykotik,"A game that I liked from the start. Once I started playing this I felt like I was actually in a real apocalypse. This game really teaches me to conserve my ammo (I can't stress enough how many times I've died because I used up all the ammo). Over time, I got scared of playing single player, so I tried multiplayer. Let me tell you, it is so fun playing with other people. There are different maps with different game modes. The game mode I like best is PvP since I can easily kill other survivors without feeling guilty. The best part about the game is the atmosphere it provides. You'll feel intimidated at times, you'll feel crazy when you play alone, and most of the time you'll just feel like giving up. I wouldn't say the game itself is scary, but it does have some horror aspects put in it. If you want a good ol' fashioned zombie outbreak game with realistic features, buy Contagion. The price is worth it. $15 for an awesome game? I wouldn't even hesitate to buying it."
