76561197983478468,Recommended,238430,11364125,"Posted: 22 July, 2014",all,Dr. Doctor,"Very good game, especially for the money.The graphics are top notch when it comes to lighting and reflections; I was very impressed by them. Textures are decent and the animation isn't very good, but when considering the size of the dev group, I think they're totally acceptable.The game has a lot to offer for 20$. There weren't as many maps whe the game first retailed (retail, not early access), but they've done good work and put in plenty enough maps to keep you occupied.There's a game mode called hunted that is very different for a zombie game but totally fun. It's human vs human, with zombies in between. The objective is to kill all other humans while becoming the last to live. Most important, however, is that there is no wait between play. When you die, you become a zombie instead of spectating. And you also get to control your own group of zombies through special skills.However, if this sounds unappealing to you, you'll probably like the escape mode. It's your traditional objective based gameplay where you must follow the hints to escape the map and the impending hordes of zombies. There's lots of shooting, zombies, and teamwork, the three essentials for a zombie game.All in all, this game is worth the buy."
