,Recommended,238430,9819667,"Posted: 14 April, 2014",all,Ylubz,"This game (in my opinion) is fun as in most game modes; extraction and escape, a lot of teamwork is needed and sharing is vital.Pros:- I dont have the best graphics card but with settings at low it still gives a good look to the game and in return gives decent performance (but it may not be the same on even less advanced PCs)- the zombies are like the typical resident evil-slow-but-dangerous-in-numbers kind of zombies (which is how I prefer zombies)- You can be a zombie and kill other live players (like in zombie panic source)- it is based off the zombie panic source engine so if you like that mod then this is somewhat similar.- zombie AI is clever as they will move to flankCons:- the player zombies are very OP (seriously I have taken out six people with one zombie before)- there are about a couple maps (3-4 but this does depend on the game mode you are playing aswell, NMRIH has custom maps so there are plenty more)- NPC zombies can be found in buggy areas.Overall I find this game very fun and a good challenge especially when I am using only a melee weapon, a lot of work has been put into this game as I will usually play periodically and there is usually a fair bit new content and the menu has been restyled and looks really cool. I think this game deserves plenty of credit for its features and hard work, and since I am a hardcore zombie gamer my natural instincts got me this game so I do recommend this game to any fans of the genre. Much better than WarZ or whatever it is called now, then again Herpes is better then that game"
