,Recommended,238430,16128668,"Posted: 1 June, 2015",all,Templar,"Great game, graphically wise i'd say the best of any FPS with zombies involved. You won't find these graphics in any other zombie game. The gore is great, and the whole atmosphere with the classic zombies is great. The game modes are great, even the Hunted game mode imo. Many complain about this game mode that there's just people walking around trying to kill each other but that's the whole point of this game mode! It's Deathmatch, in the survival world of Contagion.But don't think it's easy just to shoot someone you wander in to, the gameplay mechanics still force you to actually aim and control your shots, instead of just spraying n' praying.I came across this moment I once had in Hunted which reminded me of movie-like scenes, where this stranger came spraying at me with his AK 74U around 20 meters in front of me behind a fence, while I gave surpressing fire and we both walked sideways firing shots at each other, with me having a 9 mm pistol and obviously having a disadvantage weapon-wise. And at this one moment I decided to calmly aim for his head as I crouched, zombies around him, with my pistol while he just kept spraying like a maniac, and I ended up shooting him in the head. With zombies between us, in the dark city, this was one of the most epic moments I had so far in this game. The overall scenery in this game is somehow amazing and really hits the nail on the head for those of you who truly love zombie survival games and things alike.With that, it's epic as a zombie genre lover to actually decide to wander off while in a gunfight with a stranger, hiding in the bushes  and wandering off the city blocks, the house blocks, the piled abandoned cars, the government barricades etc etc hoping that stranger gets noticed by zombies and perhaps other strangers around, which will happen frequently, give you an advantage into getting away and finding new supplies again, and surviving. What this game is really about!!People who can't seem to get the hang out of this should rely more on actual tactics, like the one I just told you about.Really, people whining about the Hunted game mode should concentrate more on their own path while continuously watching their backs, then they will get much further and actually become able to be one of the last 3 players alive, and win the round. It's all about the TACTICS, which makes this game great as itself, because it's not just a simple shooter.All the other game modes are great too, and I've had tons of fun playthroughs on Escape for example, deciding where to hide out until extraction, while fighting off hordes of incoming zombies. And those zombies are aggressive even though they don't run! Some somehow still limb in quite a fast pace towards ya, so good aiming is a must. They're far more of a threat than the zombies in other known co-op zombie games. which really nails the pace the whole zombie genre is about. Slow zombies, yet the whole sphere is action paced.And those zombie hordes keep coming, so you better off sparing your ammo for the right heads to shoot, while scavenging for more.This game gives you movie-like experiences, and is a piece of art in itself. It reminds me a lot of all of those classic Romero zombie movies!Great game, AAA+ 10/10 in it's genre, 9.8/10 overall."
