,Recommended,238430,16488394,"Posted: 17 June, 2015",all,The Tunable Sausage,"I am not sure what all the bad reviews are about.  I will review the game, not the attitude of the developer.  Developers have lives and sometimes don't get around to doing everything on time.  How would you feel if you spend all of your time developing a game and then all you get in return is complaining and nasty reactions by entitled children who don't have the ability to make games themselves?  You would get pretty upset pretty quickly, and thats a fact (four years of customer service taught me that).  Besides, its under new management now.Anyway, I bought Contagion while it was still in Alpha and I have always had a great experience with it.  Multiplayer escape maps can be challenging, as good communication amongst your squad members is a definite necessity.  This is also the case for extraction, but less so as there are far fewer goals to achieve other than rescuing survivors.  The hunted maps are a lot of fun on full servers, and the enjoyment almost increases with fewer players as it becomes a game of cat and mouse.I have had hours of fun on LAN or over skype calls with my friends and have never regretted buying this game.  Sure, there are a few bugs occasionally, the hitboxes can be a bit sketchy sometimes, but that comes with the territory of designing a game that relies on headshots for kills (i.e. its not easy).  Its a good buy full price but a real steal on sale.  I am looking forward to the continued updates."
,Recommended,238430,16779303,"Posted: 29 June, 2015",all,Lord Fizzy,I've had a blast playing this with my friends and it's one of my favorite zombie games ever. The co-op maps have a nice classic horror atmosphere to them and can offer an enjoyable challenge with huge hordes of zombies. The panick you get when trapped by a horde of 30 zombies is a quite unique experience. And it feels like a great accomplishment the few times you manage to survive and escape a map. The pvp is also really fun and it can be difficult having to worry not only about other players but also zombies.
