76561198035098247,Recommended,238430,10946887,"Posted: 29 June, 2014",all,dwinblood,"I tried this game many months ago and it had a ways to go.   This weekend I revisited it with three other family members.   It has come a long way and is actually quite the fun game.Premise: Zombie outbreakGame Modes we tried:  Escape, Extraction, Hunted, and PanicEscape: Is much like L4D and L4D2 in the sense you're trying to get away.Extraction:  You are using your cell phone to find NPC survivors and lead them to safetyHunted:  PvP last man standingPanic:  Team Deathmatch (almost) where some players are Zombies.   It had no NPCs when we played which was the biggest thing missing, I don't know if there is an option to fix this or not.   It was okay but not that great with just 4 players due to lack of NPCs.COOL FACTOR: If you are bitten you might be infected and not realize it.   You can be walking a long and then suddenly double over and turn into a zombie.   You get 4 commands.   Vision which gives you a special vision that shows foot prints for awhile of living non-zombie people.   Roar which lets you attract other NPC zombies that will walk with you and follow you.  Blend which relinquishes control of yourself so you'll move more like the other zombies and not be obviously player controlled, you press blend again to retain control.   It also has a command (as in issue command) power which I suspect lets you tell the other NPC zombies you've attracted to do something.   NEGATIVE: In Panic mode the lone zombie player it created had no NPC zombies to order around which put him at a very distinct disadvantage.It is already a fun game, if they keep going the direction they are it becomes easier and easier to recommend the game.CONS: The cell phone, and the numeric keys were not mapped by default so for a long time I didn't know what I was supposed to be doing (no cell phone), and I couldn't toggle my weapons I'd picked up.   Once I mapped the keys this was resolved."
