,Recommended,238430,12081662,"Posted: 13 September, 2014",all,PhantomAvian,"This game has a more realistic approach to the zombie apocalypse than L4D. It's just you and other survivors, ordinary zombies, and limited ammo that you have to scrounge and scavenge. I've had a good bit of fun playing it, since it is fairly unique. It is worth noting, however, that it is a bit light on the content and features and perhaps a little rough around the edges, feeling more like an older game than a current title. I would recommend that you wait until it's on sale, and then at that point, by all means buy it.Hunted mode is PVP - the last survivor standing wins! Thus, you not only have to worry about the zombies that want your brain, but also every other gun-wielding survivor. I've been in some pretty brutal firefights - plenty of tense fun, and the most popular game mode.Escape mode is a coop puzzle mode - solve the puzzles (how do I get to <location>? where can I find a pair of bolt cutters?) and complete the objectives to escape. I recommend playing solo or with a group of people you know - I've just had better luck that way. On public servers, everyone scrambles to get the loot before it's all grabbed up, leaving zombies alive to sneak up behind everyone, getting themselves killed in their rush for loot, and not working as a cohesive team. Then, the players who are killed due to this  come back as zombies, substantially reducing the odds of survivors escaping. This mode needs to be played methodically - stick together, kill all the zombies in an area, loot, then proceed to the next area at the same time as a group. When this happens, it's pretty fun - otherwise, it's frustrating.I found Extraction mode to be kind of frustrating. Any lack of teamwork is even more problematic than in Escape, the AI survivors are dumb as rocks, and the zombie hordes are hard to keep at bay."
