,Recommended,238430,9357146,"Posted: 5 March, 2014",all,[dm]24/7,"I'm writing this short review approximately 1 month from proposed release date, so the game is still officially in 'early beta'.As a huge fan of co-op FPS (borderlands, etc) and especially zombie titles (dead island, L4D, etc) I'm very excited about this game.  Overall the game is quite polished already, but there are a few quirks (overused character models, texture clipping, etc) that spoil the immersion a little.There is limited content (I would suggest that 'escape' mode seems to be the main campaign/mode of the game but there is only one map), and there are some bits missing like zombie-climbing animations, voice acting etc but all of these seem on track for the full release.If the game follows through with its full release it has the potential to be a truly awesome game. Left 4 Dead comparisons are discouraged but unavoidable, and I for one (as a L4D fanatic) am looking forward to this. It sits somewhere between L4D and 'no more room in hell' (a slightly slower, more realistic zombie survival co-op game than L4D).Keep an eye out for the full release due some time around April 2014."
