76561197995214447,Recommended,238430,9925492,"Posted: 24 April, 2014",all,Odo,"Don't let the cheesey, ugly, and arguably derivative intro trailer fool you - Contagion is in my opinion, the definitive multiplayer zombie game. It's true that it's a bit rough around the edges, and that it definitely needs it's on going development, but there is A LOT of fun to be had here. Especially in the ""hunted"" multi-player mode. In it, up to 8 or 10 surivors are let loose in a large open area (My favorite is the massive and urban ""Barlow Square"" which comes complete with explorable multi-leveled buildings, subways, and movie theaters that can be raided for supplies, or reinforced for a last stand) before squaring off in a death match. What seperates this from your run of the mill FPS zombie death match is that not only is ammo limmited, but every shot attracts waves of the undead.Spy a player characte running across the street? Take aim, but beware... if you miss he'll simply duck into cover, while any zombies in the immediate area make a b-line toward your position.The zombies also add an interesting dimension to combat. On multiple occasions have I found myself in a stand off with an opponent with superior fire power, but his back to a wall. My strategy is to fire a bunch in the air to attract the hordes and scamper off before he can figure out what's happening. ""PLAYER WAS KILLED"" is so satisfying to see knowing that you attracted the zombies that devoured him as you scurry away through fire escapes and broken windows.If you're like me, games like Left 4 Dead and Dead Island don't truly feel like zombie games. They've got the look, but they lack the thrill of Running through alleyways with your friends, trying to make every shot count while making decisions on the fly (should we try running here? Or There? What if that leads to a dead end?)Every now and then you and a friend find youselves behind a set of doors while being pursued by a horded of zombies. You  two enter a room, quickly shut the door and nail it shut with a nail gun. There's a shotgun in the room with 6 rounds in it. Your friend happens to have a few more shells that he found but had no use for. He presses ""J"" to toss them to you just as the zombies start pounding at your barricade. ""We'll alternate fire"" The doors smash open. It's a glorious last stand.Oh, now for the negatives...the game is buggy. like I said earlier, it's rough around the edges. most of the level designs are really unintuitive and take a long time to learn your way around. Some might just be TOO big. I think some of the mechanics could use a bit of tweaking to really balance things a bit, but nothing game breaking.Oh, the sound design is fantastic.All in all, the zombie apocalypse by it's nature is going to be a bit unbalanced and dirty... just like Contagion is... still, there's something that just brings us all back to it. I definitely reccommend."
