76561198015307932,Recommended,238430,13611868,"Posted: 26 December, 2014",all,Bloodrook,"I've played a lot of zombie games, some good, some not so good.  Contagion ranks near the top of the stack of the great pile with it's great visuals, ambiance and pulse pounding intensity.  The multiple maps that change each time you play make this a fantastic experience in FPS's.  Playing alone is VERY difficult, so be sure to have a good group of friends to help you fight your way through many of the maps.  Barlowe Square is especially difficult, as is extraction.  Be careful not to get yourself trapped in a house while being swarmed by zombies.  You can't push your way through and ammunition resources are limited.  Speaking of ammo, head shots are the only thing that take down the shambling dead, so pick your shots carefully.  You don't necessarily have to wipe out an entire level of zombies (not nearly enough ammo for that) and sneaking is helpful.Things I would personally like to see improved is more variety in the zombie skins, more melee weapons and more health kits, even if they were just bandages giving you partial health.  However, my critiques are small, and overall this is a great game."
