,Recommended,238430,7770927,"Posted: 26 November, 2013",all,The RaptoLobster,"Contagion, a game (currently in beta) created by the makers of the incredible mod Zombie Panic: Source, brings you an incredible and unique experience.The Pros: Unique gameplay brings you a refreshing experience of what it would really be like in a zombie apocalypse. Whether you're fighting other players while avoiding zombies, or working with them to escape or defend locations, it's always a blast.Random generation makes every playthrough different in some way, guns and ammo spawn in different locations and objective modes can change every time with different paths and areas. The phone with objectives and maps is an awesome concept too.Play as a zombie and blend into AI hordes or sneak up on humans to snag a bite. With player controlled zombies, it brings a continually terrifying threat that forces you to watch your back constantly.Cons: While this game is still in beta and can't yet be fully judged, it does lack maps. The random generation helps but there are currently only three maps you can play on. Game is still being optimized, recent patch helped a lot.TL;DR All in all, a fantastic game that is definitely worth $15 even in beta!"
