,Recommended,238430,10685555,"Posted: 22 June, 2014",all,TWD Kenny,"I really do enjoy this game a lot. Although it has some problems. To start off, I want to say that one of the biggest reasons that was a big let down for me is that I checked the server browser and NOTHING popped up. I removed EVERY single filter and NOTHING popped up. Note that I just bought this game today and I'm playing it at a pretty decent time in the day (i.e. it's not early in the morning or very late at night). Set aside that, it's basically a singleplayer game unless someone decides to host a server. I would also like to point out that the load times are extremely slow, they are scraping L4D2's load times. They are THAT bad. Anyways, when I started the map, I noticed very quickly how dynamic the map looked. What I didn't expect was to see a very diverse map with loads of time built into it. After looking around and trying to scavenge some weapons, I found and shot my very first zombie. What I was unhappy to hear was that there is no such dismemberment that can occur with a pistol OR an assault rifle (I haven't found the shotgun yet). Dismemberment to me is a key factor of a zombie game as it really makes you feel like you just shot that zombie's head off or you just shot that zombie's arm off. No, that feeling did not come with this game, sadly. Reguardless of the dismemberment, the models looked very nice and I liked the mostly interactive environment. Being made in the source engine, like half-life or Left 4 Dead, it took after most of the menu screens, blood effects, and the overall world looked similar to something you'd see in L4D or HL which is kinda repetitive to me considering I play most to all of Valve's games which are made in the Source engine. Set aside the how the textures and the models look, I want to talk about the gameplay. What I really liked about this game was how they stuck to their words by saying this was a game that was supposed to be like if a zombie appocolypse actually happened. I can honestly feel like this is how it would feel like. What makes this game a lot different from any other zombie shooting game is that you really have to consider your approach to complete your mission/goal. You mostly have 2 options, go guns out, shooting every single zombie you see and trying to get done with your mission as quick as you can. Or you can do the most recommended method; stick with the shadows, conserve your ammunition, take out enimies that absolutely HAVE to be taken out, and get done with your mission reguardless of the time. I personally chose option A the first time I played this game because I was still trying to figure out the map and find my way around the places, which it did work untill I got trapped in a store with zombies surrounding me from the outside and on the inside. Nonetheless I absolutely loved this game and enjoyed this game quite a bit because it really does make me feel like I'm in a zombie appocolypse. 8/10"
