76561198105445916,Recommended,238430,31478067,Posted: 30 April,all,Fugitive Mind,"EDIT: Game continuously crashes despite lowering graphics and verifying files. This is incredibly annoying!What can I say about Contagion? Besides some partially wonky controls, a lack of a campaign, and outdated graphics, it's a lot of fun if you have a friend or two to play with. However, the community is pretty much dead and those still in the game are toxic; you NEED to play with friends.The gameplay is well-designed and quite fun/challenging, though the difficulty is clearly made with coop in mind. Headshots look and feel phenomenal, and finishing a map is satisfying. The addition of Steam Workshop is just a bonus to a surprisingly good formula. Pick Contagion up on sale; you won't regret it."
76561198044574067,Recommended,238430,8990290,"Posted: 5 February, 2014",all,KyleofKerbin,"This game overall is good. I give it an 8/10. You may be asking why I don't be a pansy and give a 10/10. I'm here to tell you why not only that this game is great, but also about its weaknesses.Let's begin with the strengths. Graphics: 10/10 Very Good! They're very detailed.. making me want to blow even more brains apart. xD Sound: 10/10 Great Sound! The details and the time put into even the most basic of sounds is fantastic! They really aren't OP in your assistance like The Last of Us, but they're not so unhelpful that they don't do anything like the newest CoD games. Gamemodes: 8/10 Good! Overall, the 3 primary gamemodes that are seen are great, EXCEPT Escape. Escape is where you escape from a building filled with hoardes of zombies. After about 10 minutes of playing this gamemode, I'm already searching for a server that has players on it that has the FANTASTIC Hunter gamemode! Escape is basically an order of events like a play or drama that you MUST FOLLOW EVERY TIME. And, even worse, there's only ONE MAP! Now, onto that great Hunter gamemode! Hunter is where not only are you trying to kill all the zombies after you, BUT YOU ALSO CAN KILL PLAYERS! :D This mode gets REALLY FUN when you encounter other players. You might need a Mic and turn on your VoiceChat option before you play this or face getting murdered the very second someone sees you. >:)Now, onto this game's weaknesses. The BIG THING is Escape mode! IT'S BORING! After you've played it once, you'll most likely be reluctant to play it again, even with friends! Overall, this gamemode gets a 5.5/10 for me. Another weakness is some sounds are NON-EXISTANT! xD For example, when I call a hoarde of zombies to my location(to do this press R), there's a cool animation, BUT NO SOUND! LOL The final weakness I have to say about this game is NOT ENOUGH DIVERSITY IN ZOMBIES. There are only(I think) 7 types of zombies! D: So, after a while, you learn the abilities of all the zombies and can usually predict what they are going to do. Now, the AI does mix up stuff every so often, but it's not enough to give the zombies enough diversity to make them COMPLETELY unpredictable.If you've read this review to here, here's a free cookie for your Cookie Clicker. :)  -----|* * * |-----Thanks for reading this review! I hope this convinces you on your decision to buy this! :D"
