,Recommended,238430,8438802,"Posted: 30 December, 2013",all,hsmoke,"As far as Early Access games go, Contagion is more or less a bug free, and fairly polished experience. It's just missing something. Alot of somthings. A huge amount of somethings.So far, the Beta offers 3 game modes, Escape, Hunt and Exctraction, all of which are excatly what it says on the tin. And out of all of these, none of them actually require teamwork, strategy or survival. For a game that does brand itself as a survival experience, there is no surviving to be done, other than kill zombies and don't get your brains blown out by your team mates. So unlike Zombie Panic: Source, weight and being outnumbered are no longer issues. You can literally kill off an entire horde by yourself, without using pr0 MLG SkiLLz. So far I have had one team-like experience, which was later ruined by my team-mate blasting my head all over the floor with a Hunting Rifle.However, this game isn't all bad. It's very pretty, and dynamic, and lots of areas on the maps (all three of them) are accesible and can be interacted with, and they are not easily exploited. Whilst playing, I also felt some genuine panic and struggle. Sadly, not over the zombie, but more so the fact the rest of the bloodthirsty server was after me. And they were much better players. ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥s.Overall, Contagion is a huge leap from Zombie Panic: Source but sadly it does not borrow enough from it. However, the game is still just in Beta and more maps, weapons and mechanincs will be added sooner or later (please, please, PLEASE.)+ Lovely dynamic environments.+ Well thought-out character lore, the game makes good use of the little story-telling oppurtunities online games have+ Very well polished for an Early Access game.- Really, there isn't much to do.- Survival and Teamwork opportunities are not very well enhanced, you could plow through a horde by yourself.7/10"
