,Recommended,238430,11916223,"Posted: 29 August, 2014",all,AngrySkull,"The thinking man's L4D.  My favorite game mode 'Escape' has you and up to seven other players cooperating to escape from the map, which is dynamically arranged with new paths and objectives every time you play.Ammo conservation and trigger discipline is absolutely critical, you can't just mindlessly run into a room full of zombies and hope to survive without backup, you never know where the next box of bullets will be.  The frenetic horde-style action of L4D is replaced with a somewhat more thoughtful pace, you have time to realize that you have three bullets left, and you know you'll have to open another door to maybe find more ammo, or a room full of zombies, and ideally they aren't going to break through it while you're considering your options.Teammate cooperation becomes not only beneficial, but it is required for success, as each player has a very limited supply of ammunition, and whatever weapons they've picked up along the way.  Your guns, one of which you'll spawn with, the rest need to be found as they spawn randomly, have to be manually reloaded, and you'll need headshots if you hope to kill enough zombies to get through the next room.  Melee weapons are an option, if you've found any, but the speed of lifting your axe to swing it, chopping an enemies arm off, to have them continue attacking you, leaves you open to attack from more zombies behind you.The randomly appearing obstacles through each map include things like: locked doors; you found a key right? Fires; This hallway is on fire, did anyone find a fire extinguisher?  Chained up doors; damn!  There's got to be some bolt cutters somewhere...So, you ran out of ammo, fell into a fire, and got trapped against a locked door while a horde of zombies came rushing in?  No problem!Dying in coop has a consolation prize, you die and become a zombie!  Now you can punish your erstwhile companions for having gotten to that ammo before you did, not helping you find a fire extinguisher, and not shooting those zombies that were attacking you!  After all, that was probably what caused your death, right?  Every player that has died is now on a team of zombies, to coordinate their attack and prevent the players from accomplishing their objectives to escape.All in all, killed a zombie with a wrench and died in a fire 10/10 would buy again"
