,Not Recommended,238430,7692039,"Posted: 18 November, 2013",all,Viktor_Rummage,"Contagion: a masterpiece thrown into the gutter and smashed right into pieces. My criticisms you ask? I'll give you my criticisms alright! When I initially purchased this game I was under the impression that the game would deliver some challenges with its content by being possibly overrun by tens and thousands of zombies while completing objective based maps that tested the strengths and virtues of my team. Well, I guess the whole being overrun thing didn't happen exactly as I previously thought. I'd say the mere fact I can't even hit the zombies' head due to the lack of an accurate hit box is enough for a gamemode itself. That's right, have fun trying to headshot zombies that squirm out of place everytime you have your ironsight accurately stationed at their forehead, it won't happen -- even if your ping is fantastically at 20 or less! The mobs, zombies, in this game are fantasically bugged beyond all belief with their seizure-like squirms that run in abundance throughout the packs of zombies in the game. As far as spawning new zombies in the game, I don't think there are many spawn points for new zombies, I actually think once you kill one they're dead for good again. I did like the running animation of your character while in first person, why with your arms extended upwards to your right while holding your handgun running like a squad member, who needs quality game mechanics when you can just watch your character run all day long looking cool!Continuing on, let's talk about the attention to detail needed within this game, especially while playing objective mode. Have fun trying to find your way around the map trying to complete vaguely written objectives that'll surely take you hours to finally find and complete. It literally took my friend and I several hours, about 2 hours in fact, to finally find an important key needed to unlock a door in the first objective based map in the game, especially with little to no clue or even a semblance of a clue as to where to go. Now, I understand the need for a survival oriented sense of dread and hopelessness within a zombie game, but to have players running around the first half of a map endlessly for hours is just plain griefing the player base in general. A sort of indication on where to go, even a tiny general one, goes a long way while still keeping that frightful atmosphere of dread and despair. So besides being clueless in this game, I also noticed that every single zombie resembles a main character within the game, so you won't have to die to see yourself reincarnated as a flesh devouring rot head, you'll shoot a couple of them before you do so, not a unique feature at all. Another issue I had with the game is its lack of administrative features given to its players. There is no voting system in place to vote kick griefers, change maps, or even restart a current level. There's nothing at all besides possibly using console commands.While I can understand this game is still in its infancy, technically beta/alpha level, the game does currently lack in a lot of content such as the amount of maps within the game, only 4 maps currently, and the MANY bugs that currently plague the game. I've only really mentioned a handful of bugs I've noticed so far but I'm sure you'll find more once you purchase this game. Another thing that really annoyed me after the fact I bought this game was the falsly advertised store page for the game when I first bought it stating that the game is in early access, which would imply it's in beta status not a seemingly preliminary alpha access. On a final note, if you ever get the chance to breeze through the game's forum page, you'll noticed a bunch of self-righteous devs who denounce any little criticised comment about their dear game and instantly shun what fanboys the game does have. I don't recommened this game to anyone, at least at the current moment where the game is stil lacking a stable environment to play in."
