,Not Recommended,238430,8790665,"Posted: 20 January, 2014",all,[BT]SirGoodMood,"Rating 6/10Yet another zombie themed game.The game consists of three game modes, Hunter, Extraction, Escape, each with one map.The gameplay is nice. Much slower paced and deliberate compared to the Left 4 Dead series, it distinctly lacks that 'arcade-y' feel of firing hundreds of bullets into swarms of weak zombies that you mmow down by the dozens. Instead, in this game, headshots are all that matter. Shots to the body are very negligible in terms of damage, meaning if you're swarmed, you better get out of there as soon as you can.This poses a problem, given that the head is a fairly small target, even small amounts of lag will make you miss your shots or cause the zombies to jitter around, preventing you from lining up your shots. If you can find a stable server, stick to it, it'll pay off in the end.The game is fun for the first couple of run throughs, the randomly generated aspects of the map is limited to a couple of doors being inaccessible on one run, and being breakable on another, or the location of key items being in one room as opposed to another room. This is fine I suppose, but makes for very tedious gameplay since you often find yourself running back and forth trying to find things, rather than being able to progress through the level.It's an okay game, but definitely not worth the price at the moment. It's a very short game with little replay value."
