76561198032528294,Not Recommended,238430,10786758,"Posted: 25 June, 2014",all,Warriorsage,"Sometimes there are bad games with good intentions.  This is one of those.For awhile Contagion sat on my Wishlist, being watched.  I read the reviews and stayed away, but still, it sat there because I have most zombie games worth owning.  It went down to five bucks, and I picked it up.  It's a good thing I waited, because that's all it's worth.Everything about this game screams that some game dev interns at a college somewhere did it in their spare time, and packaged it as quickly as they could just to have something to sell.  It's a bizarre mishmash of the zombie mode in Call of Duty, the old Resident Evil games, and Left 4 Dead.Firstly, did you watch that video when the store page opened?  I hope you enjoyed it, because that's all the story you're going to get.  It's also the prettiest graphics you're going to get.  We don't play games like this for story, necessarily, so let's move on.The sound isn't anything special, and is low budget and forgettable.One of the features of the game is the ability to use a cellphone.  You'll get text messages on where to go.  The only problem is once I hit the button of ""recommended settings"" in the graphics options, the cellphone's text was too large for me to read - at 1080p resolution.  So, basically, this neat little feature was useless.The maps are few, you've probably already read that elsewhere.  Basically instead of making numerous maps, they made a couple, and randomized which gates would be open to provide routes through the map objectives.  It's not a terrible idea, I'm sure it saved them lots of time they spent on - nothing.Your weapons are varied but aren't particularly satisfying.  The zombies have few animations, get stuck on things constantly, and have no ragdoll physics, so a shotgun blast has no kick, it simply does damage.  1990's, anyone?The combat's critical in a game like this.  I found it kind of refreshing having to use ironsights on my gun since there's no crosshair.  You can configure your character's bob when they run, and the look and ironsight speeds separately.You get a flashlight on some weapons.  You can tell they tried to make the lighting effects cool and bounce off different colors on different surfaces.  What it turns out to be is bizarre effects that make you think you're viewing the world through a riot mask that has grime all over it.  Almost useless.If there's one thing you have to get right in a zombie game, it's the headshots.  Unfortunately, the hitboxes are unreliable.  Much of the time you'll shoot right where your gun is pointing.  Sometimes you'll score a surprising headshot.  But then there are those times when you are DEAD CERTAIN you scored a headshot, but you missed the quirky hitbox.  This is completely unforgivable in a game that specifically limits the ammo it gives you.Melee is a joke.  There are multiple melee weapons in the game.  As far as I could tell, you cannot score a headshot with them, and they all do exactly the same damage - 3 swipes per zombie.  Since the zombie animations aren't terribly well synced with the damage, they'll frequently get you when you know they shouldn't have, and vice versa.In a mode that was basically Call of Duty boards-on-windows, one vending machine spews weapons at slow intervals when you hit the buttons, one spews ammo fairly regularly - almost always for guns you don't have.  It was almost fun.I never did get around to playing on servers with other people.  You can solo, technically.  You'll sometimes require bolt cutters or fire-extinguishers to proceed, and since the game is ""realistic"", you'll wind up backtracking in a game with no map.I tried the other map, and at one juncture I emptied 8 or 9 shots into a zombie at POINT BLANK RANGE, and hit nothing but air.  That was it for me.  I have better games to play with friends, and so do you."
