76561197965074601,Not Recommended,238430,9193750,"Posted: 20 February, 2014",all,UNDERHILL,"Imagine an updated Zombie Master (you played that one, right? remember the Winchester level?) has developed a mutagenic virus and injected it into a really bad RPG and you've got CONTAGION.Though there are several map modes none of them really contain any new ideas. There are also only a very small handful of maps. One map mode has you running around looking for clues to get through the level which sounds fun and would smack of left4dead if your companions had any reason whatsoever to want to have you around. Anyone who knows the level already can more or less just ignore everyone else and complete all the objectives leaving new players to wonder how the game is actually played without huge amounts of trial and error or reading guides. It does not teach itself well and the targets can be very obscure.That the map system consists of a PDA showing very little information does not help to soften the ""alone in a crowd"" feeling when the team has already completed several objectives and you spawn at the start wondering where to go or being blocked off from the team by crowds of zombies. Your entry to the level is hardly ever soft.The choice of key mappings also leaves much to be desired. It is very easy to accidentally drop your weapon if you are used to the controls from other common games. Add to this the fact that targeting and picking up or interacting with things requires the utmost precision and you've got one hell of a headache.Contagion has an interesting concept - which was already very successfully done by left4dead - and adds nothing new to the genre. It could easily be said that it goes back a few steps. This has the feeling and polish level of one of those FPS mods that sits in small-team development-hell for years with almost nothing getting done on it.The graphics are indeed quite passable. The Christmas/snow level has quite a nice feel to it reminiscent of neighborhood charm of several of the similar half-life community maps from long ago.Again, nothing new.4/10."
