,Not Recommended,238430,14460241,"Posted: 14 February, 2015",all,Domino,"I like its aspects of realism and teamwork.I don't like its lack of hitscan and animation sync. If you're close to a zombie, it literally hits you two seconds before it actually swings its arm, even with a low latency. Ironsights aim tends to be off with some weapons, and since a core 'feature' of the game is a need to conserve ammo, most of its bugs tend to be very counterproductive and make the game nearly impossible in some situations.I also REALLY don't like the lack of configurable options. No option to turn off friendly fire even in strictly cooperative mode, no flexible dedicated servers, nothing. There are four difficulties, and they all affect the same thing without any variance: Damage taken & dealt, amount of ammo to be found, etc.I'm not getting my hopes up with this game, yet. It seems to be one of those types of games fitting under a 'great idea, poor execution' category, but the game itself is still far from being 'complete' and is being worked on at a gradual pace, so maybe after several more patches and a few more updates, I'll be able to recommend this, but for now, I'd recommend staying away."
