76561198009351189,Not Recommended,238430,13152312,"Posted: 29 November, 2014",all,Angrysquirrel,"In my opinion, this is the only first person game that truly captures the tension of surviving a zombie apocalypse.   You have limited resources in terms of ammo, weapons, and supplies and everyone needs to stick together to have a greater chance of survival.  Since ammo is limited you need to headshot zombies unless you want to risk infection and fight hand to hand. The maps are dark and foreboding.  The weapons look great and the sounds are crisp and accurate.  The zombie models and sounds are also good too.On the downside, there aren’t a lot of maps to play right now.  There also isn’t much interactivity with the map objects either.  The developers said they will be releasing more downloadable content with two more maps (which I believe brings it to three more from the original build), and a few more weapons.There are also some technical problems as well. The zombie spawning is bugged.   For example, on the prison map you are spawned as a zombie and cannot get to the survivors because you’ve spawned in a portion of the map the survivors don’t have access to.   Other times you are spawned into a place on the map as a zombie almost on the complete opposite side of the map where the survivors are.  There’s no waypoints as a zombie to the survivors, so unless you know the map really well you will be out of the action for a long, long time.There is some occasional, inexplicable in game lag.  Not sure if it’s a limitation of the engine they used but as a survivor trying to headshot zombies, the lag will cause you to miss and you could become lunch and then turned.There are only a few game modes right now.  One is a way point mode where you find things to aid in an escape, and another mode where you escort survivors to an extraction zone.  The developers have said that more modes are coming.The development cycle on this game has been really slow.  Sometimes no updates are released for a month or more.  The developers say they are bringing more people into the team so hopefully when that happens updates will pick up.I would recommend this game if you can handle the above problems.Update 02/23/16I no longer recommend this game.  It appears the company has abandoned it, as evidenced by the regular price drops into the bargain basement and no more updates.  All the company spokesperson on Steam talks about are free giveaways and playing other people's games.  The game is still littered with bugs which will likely never be fixed.I wish I had never bought this game. It is essentially the same as the free game zombie panic source  but with game breaking bugs and no support."
