,Recommended,238430,10166041,"Posted: 18 May, 2014",all,OneJibmoNation,"Beats the *ISH* outta the L4D series. Much less ""arcade""y, yet not too much realism where it takes the fun out of it. You've got coop objective-based maps which are fun (only thing is they can be a bit confusing at first if you're new as far as what exactly you have to do, this game will not hold your hand through everything and give you hundreds of annoying popups and markers). Then you have a pvp + pve mode where you face against zombies in the environment as well as other players. You are not a human pincussion in this game like in others, one or two well placed shots WILL kill you. Death is permanant for the round in both modes, though you do spawn as a zombie that can blend in and behave just like all the others which is pretty fun stalking other players in the shadows and taking out that damned camper that just killed you! Unlike most mainstream zombie games, headshots are almost required to take down a zombie (but for the most part take them out in one hit)Graphics in this game for a Source engine game are pretty damn good! The team seems to have spent a lot of work with the basic mechanics/feel of the game where you can barely tell that it's Source. Weapon moves slightly with mouse movement (like in BF3/4 and Arma series), there are no crosshairs, you have iron sights. When you look down you see feet, no floating in the air over nothing like a lot of games like to do. Heads and limbs blow off of zombies where you shoot them, dynamic lighting/shadows, etc etc.I'm really surprised this game isn't more popular. The developers of this game are the same team that brought us Zombie Panic Source mod, so they're not a big dev company backed by big publishers (or even valve). Even though the game is released, the team is still working on bringing out more maps and content, and even a reworking of the current character models. Every friday they host a livestream on twitch where they talk to the community and answer questions which is pretty damn cool. You can tell they are an old school dev studio like Unknown Worlds and valve was back in the half-life 1 days where 99% of new content and features come out in free updates, so what you see here is not all you're going to get!"
