,Recommended,238430,10175412,"Posted: 19 May, 2014",all,CooperTeam,"Contagion isn't just another 3D First Person Shooter. This particular game is more of a ""What If..."" type game where you are put in a ""Zombie Infestation"" situation and you have to figure out what you would do under (such-in-such) circumstances. Each game only gives you limited items to start with and you have to look for other weapons and accessories as you progress into the game.The game itself offers single as well as multiplayer modes. Most of the multiplayer is about helping each other out, but if you are more of a ""Naw, you're on your own"", that's fine to. The game also offers many kinds of ways you can deal with the zombies as well as create strategies for yourself on how you can get by with only a monkey-wrech and a cell phone to start with.If you ever wanted to see what it's like to be in a ""Zombie Infestation"" world, this game offers that situation to you. Not a whole lot of areas to play with, but the areas themelves offer different ways on how you can handle the situation given to you. I will say that everytime I play, it's not easy avoiding the zombies at first while trying to find cool weapons, but once you do manage to find say a shotgun, and enough ammo, you're pretty much set for a while.One thing you will have to get used to is that there is no crosshair or targetting dot, you have to ""guess"" whether or not you are aiming perfectly. To me, that's ideal since even in real life, even if you get a gun, you don't automatically get a crosshair.Overall a good game that makes you think as well as teaches you how to survive a zombie infested world.(STRATEGY ALERT) Like they say in the movies, aim for the head, once shot to the head and that's it. Shots to the chest or limbs only slow it down as well as make it angry."
