,Recommended,238430,11913352,"Posted: 29 August, 2014",all,Eidolonai,"After a couple of hours into this game i decided to give my opinion on it in review form to help others decide over the course of the free/sale weekend [may not be on sale during time of reading]. Upon my journey to the review page i found many negative reviews and it left me shocked. For starters i did not play this game during beta so i am unaware to its supposed negative changes from beta to release that most negative reviewers criticize.My first game in Contagion was a very positive experience, the other players helped each other and team work was apparent, but really I do not care for an online experience in a zombie game but rather its relation to gameplay, sound, and realism. So that is what i am going to cover.GAMEPLAY [8/10]: As a zombie enthusiast I would say Contagion plays like a proper zombie survival game and it is up there in terms of ideas and gameplay. Shots to a walkers head is exciting and fun, guns feel real and its a joy to use them all, melee weapons feel powerful and are great to use in order to concerve ammo though can feel loose at first, and above all the atmosphere is great. Bunkering down in a house to find supplies, rushing yourself as a horde bashes its way in downstairs is a stand-alone amazing experience. Most times I found myself breaking a window and jumping out from a height to save my life rather than be eaten by the horde. The objective based gameplay in Contagion is also refreshing. The game has a minimul HUD, adding to the immersion, with the use of a phone as your source for guidance [whether it be a map or other players 'texting' each other their accomplishments]. Players do not also have the fear of a lowering health bar, but also the risk of infection that can turn an online game upside down for the better, maybe even leaving your team in a panic. Overall the gameplay is great and i honestly would not change it for anything nor compare it to another game or mod.SOUND [7/10]: Sound design in Contagion is immersive and feels well put. Each gun has its own distinctive punch and sounds great put with the pop of a zeds head. However, sound related to melee can feel bland and does not seem to match the powerful feel of swinging a bat or axe, but nevertheless it works. Explosions are highly similar to most games using the source engine but are actually well put together [L4D being an example of 'loose' or 'laggy' explosions]. Atmospheric sounds and the groans of zeds are well placed and adds to the games immersion if wearing a headset. Breaking glass, banging on doors, and footsteps are other great sounds that adds to this games overall feel and atmosphere, causing an improved experience.REALISM [9/10]: Gameplay and sound in Contagion add to its realism intensively; however, it is the games atmosphere that makes it feel real. The level design in Contagion reveals the time and effort the dev team put into making the game. Zombies wonder the streets aimlessly and it is easy to make your way around the map in silence rather than running and gunning like most of todays zombie 'survival' games that they claim to be. The games lighting is dark and positively empty, causing the player to use the flash light which, at times, can be a pain that blinds the player but 8 times out of 10 it is an effective tool. Pickups in the game are randomly placed and can lead the player in finding items that are alien to them or endlessly searching for ammo. Overall the atmosphere of Contagion is bleak, dark, and quite scary if played correctly [no running and gunning]. It feels like an apoclypse has took place.If you're a zombie fanatic looking for an authentic experience, pick this game up. If you're a zombie fanatic looking for a co-op experience like L4D do not buy this, you will be dissappointed. If you're not a zombie fanatic, Contagion is a good starting point for you. The one thing I would like to see from this game is a supported community of modders that actively create maps and content to upload onto the workshop on a regular basis, creating endless hours of enjoyment. Overall Contagion feels real and authentic and it is the kind of objective based zombie survival game I enjoy with friends. I give this game an 8/10. For more questions, leave a comment and I will make sure to answer!"
