76561198018569069,Recommended,238430,8449448,"Posted: 30 December, 2013",all,Kobras,"Updated review, I've played this for a while now and recently came back to it after 6 months or so.  From the hours played, you can probably tell I've got my money's worth.  I'm not sure what all the whining on here is about.It's 100% accurate that there are not a lot of players for the game online.  There are about 50% fewer players than when I played it before.  However, for the most part the players that have been on there have been decent.  Generally, the fewer the players, the more cooperation you get as in ammo exchange and help.As far as development, I came back after 6 months and the game does have a couple more player models, more guns, more game modes and added maps.  So, it doesn't seem like the developer is sitting back and doing nothing.  I also dont rate a game based on developer hate, I just judge it on if the game has had new things added to it.  It has.They may need to evaluate some of the maps, because as others have noted, there are some issues with some opf them.  I noticed on the mansion escape map that players can hide behind a shop light in the attic and no one/zombies can really get to them.  That's an easy enough fix, just remove the shop light from the attic.I mentioned this a year ago and I still believe that there needs to be some sort of visual indication of what type of ammunition you are carrying.  I think this would give a visual clue that players (especially new ones- yes they are out there!) need to drop ammo they can not use for other players.  Either that, or the ammo they have horded should start to weigh them down somehow.If you buy the game on sale and play it for a while, I think it's well worth the money.  I've played it a long time and will continue to play it on and off.  I've had a lot of fun cooperating with others on escape (Although IT IS much more fun with two or three players than with eight) and hunting down other players while dodging zombies on Hunted.Is it as smooth and polished as Left for Dead 2?  No way, but it is a different type of game.  Contagion is creepier and slower than Left for Dead and I would say the paths are not as forced (which obviously leads to confusion and occasional panic).I still recommend this one on sale."
,Recommended,238430,12423017,"Posted: 9 October, 2014",all,MetalNeverDies,"So I came back and played a bit more of this game, and I'm glad I did. I was a bit unfair to it previously. Let me go through the pros and cons with you.PROS:Has a few features I've always wanted to see in a zombie game. If you're killed by a zombie, you become a zombie. (This ties into a con I'll mention later). The game handles quite well, with responsive aiming and true first person. Guns in the game are well handled, if perhaps they don't quite feel powerful as they should. The sound design for the guns, however, is excellent, everything sounds as it should.The game mode ""Escape"" is quite entertaining and worth a few hours of your time, at least.CONS:Player zombies are overpowered as♥♥♥♥♥♥ End of story. There is a lot of times where objectives are very unclear, and you can spend upwards of a half-hour searching for an objective. The AI is utterly broken and nonfunctional in some points. For zombies it works well enough, but for survivors it's completely brain-dead. AI survivors will shoot each other in the head if they cross each other's lines of fire, they will become stuck in place, and they will teleport off the map and scream ceaselessly for no apparent reason. Not to mention the whine and ♥♥♥♥♥ incessantly with the same two lines to the point of driving you mad.End score is a 6/10. If you're bored and have an excess of money, this is not the worst game you could add to your library."
