76561198082250655,Recommended,238430,14076395,"Posted: 19 January, 2015",all,frozen north,"Contagion is a very good game, and I tend to find that i can come back day after day and still have fun. That said, I dont usually spend more then an hour or two a day playing this game because of the hand full of faults that cause some problems with gameplay.pors:+very fun to play after you get the hang of the game+the fact that zombies can be killed similar to most other zombie games results in a shallow initial learning curve+the zombies pose a real threat. player zombies even more so (yes, you can be a zombie)+different weapons need different types of ammo, forcing players to share supplys+loot is generated randomly unless it is preset to spawn at a specific area+most situations can be solved through a bit of good teamwork+the game is affective at creating a scary atmosphere+controls are very effective and responsive+graphics are very goodcons:-zombies are subject to a handful of bugs that ruin immersion-good teams are rarer then winning the jackpot at the lottery-escape and extraction can a bit repetive-hunted is really just a contest to see who plays the most call of duty-lack of weapon variety (total of 3 pistols, 2 smg's, 2 shotguns, etc...)-all to often, people fail to realize that not all ammo works in the guns that there carryingpoints of interest:-feels like a more polished version of no more room in hell, although that game is free-a free dlc pack is supposed to be realesed that will include new weaponsOverall the game is very good. The games flaws do cause some problems but not enough to ruin the game. Most of my problems with the game are centered on the lack of attention and teamwork among a good chunk of the playercommunity. Focusing on the game and the quality of the game on its own, contagion deserves a solid 9/10."
