,Recommended,238430,13920754,"Posted: 10 January, 2015",all,Unconquered,"If Left 4 Dead and Killing Floor are one side of the Zombie shooter coin, which primarly focuses on fast-paced shooting action, then Contagion is the other side, focusing on scavenging, survival and a more realistic approach.This is the closest I've got a to a Walking Dead experience.The escape mode is pretty good, Barlow Square is great albiet the routes can be too hidden and difficult for newer players. Although this would be a blast playing it with known friends, I've got mostly a good play experience from the community of strangers, where we would actually work together. But once in a while you get players who will sprint away so they can scavenge everything. When your character dies, you play as a Zombie, constantly trying to overwhelm until no survivor is left. It's actually really fun, again, mainly because of the pacing. You'd spend a good 4-5 mins scouting and stalking the survivor before even trying an attack.The gameplay sure as hell needs polish. Another drawback is the voice acting. Jessica's sprinting sound could have someone in your house mistake you for watching porn.On a high note, the Graphics are as good as it gets and the ambience and soundtrack is impressive!It's clearly not worth $19.99, but decent at 5$"
,Recommended,238430,13369268,"Posted: 14 December, 2014",all,tonicmole,"Contagion is a surprisingly good FPS Zombie shooter, but suffers from extremely long levels with no check points, or ability to save even in a single player run through.  Concidering the game takes a bit to learn, you'll be replaying the same level from the beginning over and over....and over, never feeling like you have accomplisherd anything.  Frankly, this game would be 'must have' if each map was broken into multible stages which you unlocked as you moved forward.  Dying after 2 hours of gameplay and returning to the beginning is never fun.  Graphically it's not bad, and the presentation is far more professional than most other zombie games on Steam.  It really comes down to your tolerance level.At first Contagion would appear as a Left 4 Dead clone, however it quickly sets a dramatically different pace more in line with a survival horror rather than L4D's run and gun frenzy.  You explore area's and clear out the zombies, while figuring out how to move forward.  Which brings us to problem #2.  Many times you find yourself lost wandering hallways with no clear idea of what to do next.  This is par for the course for survival horror games where you can save, go eat a sandwich, and than get back to it later.  Contagion however has the save system of an areana shooter, and the gameplay of a FPS horror game.  I gaurantee if you play for a few minutes you will fall in love with Contagion.....until you die and revert all the way back to the beginning....than you will hate it.In the end it's a fun game with a cool concept, and your enjoyment depends on your tolerance for horrid save systems.  Oh, and there are these armored zombie that take a million bullets to kill.  They suck like crazy.  Contagion is fun enough, but has so much potential it will drive you insane.  With a better progress system, and fleshed out abilities (cover system, hiding, dodging) this game could become legendary."
